addBank(string,address,string).details: function that adds an organisation to the network.no check on access rights if network strength in zero

params.eth: Ethereum account of financial institution/bank as password

addBank(string,address,string).return: uint 0 if successfull,if no access rights to transaction request sender

addCustomer(string,string).details: function that adds a customer profile to network

params.DataHash: KYC details of cutomer is form of demiliter based string

addCustomer(string,string).return: uint 0 if successfull, 7 if no access rights to transaction request sender,1 if size limit of the database is reached,2 if customer already in network

addRequest(string,address).details: Add access request from financial institution/banks interested in KYC details of the customer.

params.bankAddress: Ethereum account of financial institution/bank which has tried to access KYC details of customer.

addRequest(string,address).return: bool True is request is added successfully & false if request already exists.

allowBank(string,address,bool).details: Approve/Reject KYC access request for financial institution/bank by customer

params.bankAddress: True if customer approves kyc acess request & false otherwise.

checkBank(string,address).details: function to to validate bank log in
checkBank(string,address).return: string "0" if successful ,  null if fails

checkCustomer(string,string).details: function to validate customer log in
checkCustomer(string,string).return: book true if successful ,  false if fails

getBankEth(string).return: address account if successful ,  0x14e041521a40e32ed88b22c0f32469f5406d757a if fails

getBankKYC(address).details: function to get bank KYC count
getBankKYC(address).return: uint count of KYC if successful, 0 otherwise

getBankName(address).return: string name if successful ,  null if fails

getBankReg(address).details: function to get bank reg number of bank
getBankReg(address).return: string regNumber if successful, null if fails

getBankRequests(string,uint256).details: Not used however kept for reference *

getBankRequests1(string,uint256).details: Get list of all access requests from financial institution/banks interested in KYC details of the customer.
getBankRequests1(string,uint256).return: address Ethereum account of financial institution/bank for approval/rejection and 0x14e041521a40e32ed88b22c0f32469f5406d757a if not requests are pending.

getBankRequestsCount(string,uint256).details: Get the count of KYC access request to be approved by the customer.
getBankRequestsCount(string,uint256).return: uint Count of access request pending approval/rejection from client.

getBankRequestsDetails(string,uint256).details: Not used however kept for reference *

getCustomerBankName(string).details: function to get bank name of customer

ifAllowed(string,address).details: check if financial institution/bank is authorised by client to view kyc details.
ifAllowed(string,address).return: bool True if allowed and false if not allowed

isPartOfOrg().details: function to check access rights of transaction request sender

modifyCustomer(string,string).details: function to function to modify a customer profile in database

params.DataHash: modified KYC details of cutomer is form of demiliter based string

modifyCustomer(string,string).return: uint 0 if successfull, 7 if no access rights to transaction request sender,1 if size limit of the database is reached,1 if customer profile not in database

removeBank(address).details: function that removes an organisation from the network
removeBank(address).return: uint 0 if successfull,7 if no access rights to transaction request sender,1 if organisation to be removed not part of network

removeCustomer(string).details: function to remove fraudulent customer profile from the database
removeCustomer(string).return: uint 0 if successfull, 7 if no access rights to transaction request sender,1 if size limit of the database is reached,1 if customer profile not in database

setPassword(string,string).details: function to set password for the customer
setPassword(string,string).return: book true if successful ,  false if fails

params.ifAdded: true  indicates a succesfull addition of KYC profile

updateRating(address,bool).return: 0 if successful ,  1 if bank is not found

params.ifIncrease: true if rating needs to be increased or decrease otherwise

updateRatingCustomer(string,bool).return: 0 if successful ,  1 if bank is not found

viewCustomer(string).details: function to return customer profile data
viewCustomer(string).return: string delimited KYC details of customer if successfull, Access Denied - if no access rights to transaction request sender, customer profile not in database
